text: Acanthophila alacella is a moth of the family Gelechiidae. It is known from most of Europe, the northern Caucasus, Georgia and Iran. 200px The wingspan is . Adults are on wing from July to August.UKmoths The larva feed on lichens on tree-trunks. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1839 Category:Acanthophila Category:Moths of Europe Category:Moths of Asia
